object.script:
--Color of the gauge. You may edit it as you like. r = 255 g = 50 b = 0
mx = property.getNumber('Max value') dec = property.getNumber('Digits after decimal point') p1 = math.pi / 180
function rd(num) if dec > 0 then local mult = 10^(dec or 0) return math.floor(num * mult + 0.5) / mult else return math.floor(num) end end
function onTick() spd = rd(input.getNumber(1)) a = (spd / mx * 260 - 220) * p1 x = math.cos(a) * 14 + 16 y = math.sin(a) * 14 + 17 end
function onDraw() --backround screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawRectF(0, 0, 33, 33) screen.drawCircleF(16, 16, 9)
--text screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) screen.drawTextBox(6, 14, 20, 6, spd, 0, 0)
screen.setColor(r, g, b) for i = -270, 90 do ang = i * (p1) if i > (spd / mx * 260) - 220 then screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) else screen.setColor(r, g, b) end xc = math.cos(ang) * 14 + 16 yc = math.sin(ang) * 14 + 17 screen.drawCircleF(xc, yc, 1) end screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawRectF(0, 26, 33, 33) end

sen = 0 fil = property.getText("label") em = property.getText("empty") function onTick() bat = input.getNumber(1) end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0) screen.drawClear() shag = 0.02 if h > 64 then shag = 0.01 end if h > 150 then shag = 0.005 end if bat ~= 0 then for i = 0,6.28*bat,shag do screen.setColor(50*(i/6.28),50*(1-i/6.28), 0) screen.drawLine(w/2+math.cos(i-1.57)*h/3, h/2+math.sin(i-1.57)*h/3, w/2+math.cos(i-1.57)*(h/2-3), h/2+math.sin(i-1.57)*(h/2-3)) end screen.setColor(50, 50, 50) screen.drawTextBox(0, 0, w, h, fil, 0.5, 0.5) else screen.setColor(50, 0, 0) screen.drawTextBox(0, 0, w, h, em, 0.5, 0.5) end end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() title = property.getText("Title") inactiveCircle = property.getBool("Inactive Circle") optimization = property.getBool("Optimization")
processNumber = getNum(1) maxNumber = getNum(2) minNumber = getNum(3)
oldAngle = -1 angle = math.min(2*math.pi, round(((processNumber - minNumber) / (math.abs(minNumber - maxNumber))) * 2 * math.pi, 1))
end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() if angle ~= oldAngle then w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() drawDial(angle, {w / 2, h / 2}, h * 0.9, 2, title) end end
function round(num, numDecimalPlaces) if numDecimalPlaces and numDecimalPlaces>0 then local mult = 10^numDecimalPlaces return math.floor(num * mult + 0.5) / mult end return math.floor(num + 0.5) end
function circleCoords(ang, r) return {(r * math.sin(ang)), -(r * math.cos(ang))} end
-- drawDial(angle, center ({x, y}), width/height, margin)
function drawDial(ang, cent, d, p) screen.setColor(178, 30, 30)
--screen.drawCircle(cent[1], cent[2], d / 2) if optimization and inactiveCircle then screen.drawCircleF(cent[1], cent[2], d / 2) elseif inactiveCircle then for i = ang, 2*math.pi, 0.01 do screen.drawLine(circleCoords(i, d / 2 * 0.9)[1] + cent[1], circleCoords(i, d / 2 * 0.9)[2] + cent[2], cent[1], cent[2]) end end
screen.setColor(30, 178, 30)
if optimization and ang == 2*math.pi then screen.drawCircleF(cent[1], cent[2], d / 2) else for i = 0, ang, 0.01 do screen.drawLine(circleCoords(i, d / 2 * 0.9)[1] + cent[1], circleCoords(i, d / 2 * 0.9)[2] + cent[2], cent[1], cent[2]) end end
screen.setColor(200, 200, 200)
value = round(processNumber, 1)
screen.drawTextBox(cent[1] - d / 2, cent[2] - d / 2 + 5, d, 10, value, 0, 0)
screen.drawTextBox(cent[1] - d / 2, cent[2] + d / 2 - 5, d, 10, title, 0, 0)
oldAngle = angle end
function getNum(num) return input.getNumber(num) end
